Comment:
Optimal runtime (runtime is lowest across the curves) is between 100 and 120. There seems to be a slight decrease in
runtime in this region, however it may be the scaling causing the difference to seem insignificant. After 150 runtime
seems to flatten out and even increase slightly. This may be due to the fact that the algorithm is not able to take
advantage of the additional threads and is instead spending more time on overhead. Before 100, there are spikes in runtime,
which is not optimal.